  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY!\r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n\r\nIf this may be security issue, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind feature\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nas a probe based kubelet plugin discovery mechanism been introduced at \r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/63328 , the initial implementation  \r\nsupport flat plugin socket directory, this is assuming all socket file names are unique.  \r\n\r\nas number of plugin grows in the future, it is harder to coordinate socket names cross all vendors.  \r\nwe can support hierarchical filesystem namespaces to solve this problem.  \r\n\r\n**How to name the namespaces**:\r\nthe namespace name could be\r\n```\r\n     1:1 map to vendor name,  \r\n     or plugin type name (CSI, DevicePlugin),\r\n     or combine both plugin type and vendor name.\r\n```\r\nthen socket names only need be unique within one namespace, it will\r\nbe much easier to coordinate naming within the namespace.  \r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nthe plugin socket directory looks like this:  \r\n\r\n```\r\n plugin socket directory  \r\n    |  \r\n    ----> namespace 1 \r\n                   |  \r\n                   ----->  socket1,  socket2 ...  \r\n```\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nthis already been mentioned as TODO in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/63328\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n\r\n/sig node\r\n/area hw-accelerators\r\n/cc @jiayingz @RenaudWasTaken @vishh @ScorpioCPH @sjenning @derekwaynecarr @jeremyeder @lichuqiang @tengqm @saad-ali @chakri-nelluri @ConnorDoyle @vladimirvivien \r\n",
